  "prompt": "How do you avoid a girl without hurting her, who is madly in love with you?",
  "response": "Here are some sensitive ways to handle this situation:\n\n1. Be kind but clear\n- Communicate honestly but gently\n- Directly state you don't have romantic feelings\n- Avoid giving false hope\n\n2. Set firm boundaries\n- Limit one-on-one interactions\n- Keep conversations friendly but not intimate\n- Be consistent in your behavior\n\n3. Avoid leading her on\n- Don't flirt or send mixed signals\n- Be respectful but direct\n- Don't pretend to be interested\n\n4. Maintain emotional distance\n- Reduce personal conversations\n- Keep interactions professional/casual\n- Don't share overly personal details\n\n5. Be compassionate\n- Acknowledge her feelings\n- Show understanding\n- Don't be harsh or dismissive\n\n6. Consider her emotional state\n- Be patient\n- Recognize her feelings are genuine\n- Give her space to process rejection\n\n7. If persistent, involve others\n- If she doesn't respect boundaries, involve friends or trusted mutual contacts\n- In extreme cases, seek help from appropriate authorities\n\n8. Encourage her to move forward\n- Subtly suggest she meet other people\n- Support her personal growth\n- Show that her worth isn't dependent on your romantic interest\n\nRemember to be respectful, honest, and kind throughout the process.",
